**Cooldown Class**
================

### Overview

A simple cooldown class to prevent repeated actions within a specified time frame.

### Code

```javascript
class Cooldown {
  constructor(duration) {
    this.duration = duration; // time in milliseconds
    this.lastActivation = 0;
  }

  isReady() {
    const currentTime = Date.now();
    return currentTime - this.lastActivation >= this.duration;
  }

  activate() {
    if (this.isReady()) {
      this.lastActivation = Date.now();
      return true;
    }
    return false;
  }
}
```

### Usage

```javascript
const cooldown = new Cooldown(5000); // 5 second cooldown

if (cooldown.activate()) {
  console.log("Action executed");
} else {
  console.log("Cooldown not ready yet");
}
```

